Brazilian Stock Movers: Embraer, Redecard Decline; LLX Advances

-- B y   N e y   H a y a s h i
-- 
2011-12-02T20:29:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-02/brazilian-stock-movers-embraer-redecard-decline-llx-advances.html
The following companies are having
 unusual (IBOV)  price changes in  Sao Paulo  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close of trading. Preferred
shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The Bovespa Index fell 0.4 percent to 57,885.85.  Embraer SA  (EMBR3 BS) slid 0.1 percent to 11.38 reais after
earlier rising 2.2 percent. The world’s fourth-largest plane
builder sees AMR Corp. returning “a fraction of a fraction” of
the 216 planes made by the Brazilian company that it operates,
Chief Financial Officer Paulo Penido said at a Credit Suisse
conference yesterday in  New York . AMR sought court protection
from creditors this week.  LLX Logistica SA  (LLXL3 BS) advanced 1.5 percent to 3.28
reais. The port developer controlled by billionaire  Eike Batista 
expects to sign a contract in the “coming weeks” to move
500,000 barrels of oil a day, Chief Financial Officer Leonardo
Gadelha said today in an interview in Sao Paulo.  Redecard SA  (RDCD3 BS) sank 6.4 percent to 28.73 reais.
 Brazil ’s second-biggest card-payment processor was cut to
“underperform” from “neutral” at Banco J. Safra, which cited
“stretched” valuations and increasing competition.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ney Hayashi in Sao Paulo at 
